
@startuml

' Define classes
class User {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +birthday: Date
  +address: String
}

class BusinessOwner {
  +linkedin: String
}

class PizzaRestaurant {
  +zipCode: String
  +address: String
  +phoneNumber: String
  +website: String
  +openingHours: String
}

class Pizza {
  +name: String
  +crustStructure: String
  +price: Double
  +restaurantId: String
}

class HungryCustomer {
  +deliveryAddress: String
}

class Order {
  +orderId: String
  +orderDate: DateTime
  +deliveryDeadline: DateTime
  +numberOfPeople: Integer
  +pizzasOrdered: List<Pizza>
}

class EntertainmentOrder {
  +entertainmentType: String
  +durationMinutes: Integer
  +entertainerId: String
}

class Entertainer {
  +stageName: String
  +bio: String
  +ratePer30Min: Double
}

class RestaurantEntertainerAvailability {
  +dayOfWeek: String
  +isAvailable: Boolean
}

' Inheritance
User <|-- BusinessOwner
User <|-- HungryCustomer
User <|-- Entertainer

Order <|-- EntertainmentOrder

' Associations
BusinessOwner "1" --> "0..*" PizzaRestaurant
PizzaRestaurant "1" --> "0..*" Pizza
HungryCustomer "1" --> "0..*" Order
Order "1" --> "0..*" Pizza
Order "1" --> "0..*" EntertainmentOrder
Entertainer "1" --> "0..*" RestaurantEntertainerAvailability
Entertainer "1" --> "0..*" PizzaRestaurant

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Relationships:

- **User** is the base class for **BusinessOwner**, **HungryCustomer**, and **Entertainer**.
- **BusinessOwner** owns one or more **PizzaRestaurants**.
- Each **PizzaRestaurant** offers multiple **Pizzas**, which are unique due to being associated with a specific restaurant.
- **HungryCustomer** places **Orders**, which can be standard or **EntertainmentOrders**.
- **EntertainmentOrder** is linked to exactly one **Entertainer**.
- **Entertainer** has availability for each **PizzaRestaurant** they work with, per day of the week.

